workflow.name: Convert inbound lead data from Webhook to AI-qualified Asana tasks

parameters.content:
## üéØ AI-Powered Lead Enrichment & Qualification

### How it works
This workflow automates lead enrichment and qualification using RocketReach and OpenAI. When a lead is submitted via webhook, it enriches the data with professional contact details, validates data quality, scores the lead using AI based on seniority and fit, and automatically creates tasks in Asana for high-quality leads while notifying your team via Slack.

### Setup steps
1. **Connect credentials**: RocketReach API, OpenAI API, Asana OAuth2, and Slack API
2. **Configure webhook**: Copy the webhook URL from the trigger node and integrate it into your lead capture system
3. **Customize scoring logic**: Adjust the AI prompt in "AI Lead Scoring" to match your ideal customer profile
4. **Set thresholds**: Modify confidence (0.6) and score (6) filters based on your quality standards
5. **Test**: Send a sample lead with `first_name`, `last_name`, `company`, `job_title`, `company_domain`, and `linkedin_url`

## üì• Data Ingestion & Normalization
Receives lead data via webhook and structures it into a clean format for enrichment. Extracts key fields like name, company, job title, and LinkedIn URL.

## üîç Lead Enrichment & Quality Check
Enriches leads with RocketReach to find professional emails and phone numbers. Calculates confidence scores based on email grade (A-D) and filters out low-quality data before AI scoring.

## ü§ñ AI Lead Scoring & Filtering
Uses GPT-4o-mini to intelligently score leads (1-10) based on job seniority, company size, and data quality. Assigns priority levels and filters leads below threshold (score < 6).

## ‚úÖ Task Creation & Notifications
Creates Asana tasks for qualified leads and sends Slack notifications to your sales team. Disqualified leads also trigger notifications for tracking purposes.

## üîê Credentials & Security
**Required credentials**: RocketReach API key, OpenAI API key, Asana OAuth2, Slack API token.

‚ö†Ô∏è **Important**: Replace the hardcoded RocketReach API key in the HTTP node with a credential. Never expose API keys in shared workflows.

The IF node can be used to implement binary conditional logic in your workflow. You can set up one-to-many conditions to evaluate each item of data being inputted into the node. That data will either evaluate to TRUE or FALSE and route out of the node accordingly.

This node has multiple types of conditions: Bool, String, Number, and Date & Time.
